1. Clone or download the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/medical-symptom-checker.git
cd medical-symptom-checker
2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Run the app
python app.py

On the first run, the app will automatically train the model from the included dataset and save model files inside the models/ folder.

Datasets

This repository includes:

DiseaseAndSymptoms.csv → used for training the disease prediction model
Disease precaution.csv → used to show basic precautions for the top predicted disease
Notes
The app is designed as an educational machine learning project.
It is not a real medical diagnosis system.
The model predictions depend on the quality and structure of the included dataset.
